//Bone marrow edema â€“ Characterization I - Proximal humerus

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Bone marrow edema' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled and selected by default
And 'Proximal humerus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lateral clavicle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Scapula' checkbox is enabled
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled


When I select 'Proximal humerus' checkbox
Then 'Hill-Sachs-Lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Reverse Hill-Sachs-Lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Humeral head' checkbox is enabled
And 'Greater tubercle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lesser tubercle' checkbox is enabled

And 'Subchondral' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal' radio button is enabled
And 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Diffuse-patchy' radio button is enabled
And 'Subcortical edema formation (fine subchondral lines)' radio button is enabled
And 'Soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickened and edematized synovialis' checkbox is enabled
